rComments: Dr. Deb remains one of the best profs I've ever had. She takes student feedback halfway through the semester and actually improves the classes with the feedback. Great class discussions. Clear with the expectations for papers and the class generates a list of what will be on final in lecture making studying for this class easier than other finals.

So passionate both about the course topics and about the wellbeing of the students in the class. Genuinely felt like I could approach her with anything. Tutorial is large part of grade, but is relatively interesting and useful. Such a caring and exciting professor! I skipped a lot of lectures in 1st year, but was sad when I had to miss one of hers.

Dr. Cowen cares deeply about the subject matter she teaches. She understands the needs of students both financially and mentally, and is more than willing to accommodate based on said needs. Her course content is intersectional and relevant and she is extremely easy to get in touch with outside of class.
her personality and character truly changed my life. she's such an amazing person whose passion was way too contagious to not catch
amazing professor, and extremely accessible outside of the classroom, she really took the time to reply and be active in her student's success.

a great prof! very engaging lectures and interesting assignments. the last assignment requires you to read a novel, and the assingment is 3 small parts which is especially appreciated at the busy end of semester.
Best professor of my undergrad experience

Prof passionate & friendly; orders pizza for reading sessions. Course is not about urban planning or social "science", but much more on urban problems such as inequality & gentrification. Course material is politically left-leaning, but prof did a good job presenting it neutrally. Didn't learn much, but cant say it didnt change the way I see things

Prof Cowen is amazing- had her for GGR124 first year and was constantly impressed by how much she clearly cared for students, even in large classes like GGR124. Definitely looking forward to taking more of her courses in the future- Deb Cowen is hands down the best prof I've had at U of T so far!
Great lecturer. Ggr124 was kind of a bird course. There is some reading, but not challenging whatsoever. Recommend this prof for a breather from the mass of inarticulate professors at uoft.

Best class I've taken at UofT. Very inspiring (both the lectures and the Prof). Learn cool things and very easy to get good grades that's because the assignments aren't difficult but they're also very interesting so you actually do them. Professor is really approachable. Readings are relevant, mainly news articles. Enjoy this course!
Made a geography course about city planning to in a politics course. Learned nothing new or interesting.

She is an excellent professor who genuinely cares about her students. Her passion for what she teaches makes her class very interesting and enjoyable. go to her office hours or reading room if you can!!

Shes one of my favorite professors. She doesnt assign many readings. She talks with enthusiam, she had made me fall a bit in love with geography. Due to taking her class, im more aware of the urban crises going around in the world. Her lectures are very enjoyable.

The professor that got me into loving my Geography major at U of T. She's very passionate about her work and it translates into her teaching. Loved both her classes! Highly recommend taking her classes if it's possible.
She may be a nice person, but she does not have the best teaching skill in the world.

Deborah is a great professor. She provides thorough notes which follow the lecture. It's a 2hr class and sometimes she forgets to give breaks bc she's so engaged, so prepare for stiff legs. The assignments aren't the run of the mill papers which makes them interesting, marking is kind of open ended though. Overall great course

Great Prof! Full of energy! Very engaging! If you are looking for a fun prof and a fun course, take GGR124 with Prof Cowen!  This is a great elective. You don't need to be a social science student to do well, but be ready to participate in lectures and tutorials...

Good at getting students involved with group work during class. Awesome lectures, encourages discussion, interesting readings. Passionate about her work. Encouraged me to continue my studies in grad school.
If all profs were like Dr. Deb, UofT would be a happier place.  Biggest gem ever.
Great teacher, extremely helpful and really nice!
arguably one of the best classes UofT has to offer due to the prof, her elctures and course content. a must take for students in every range of study.

Amazing professor, very understanding and truly cares for her students. She upholds academic integrity and ensures that everything is done fairly for the students in midst of the TA strike. She's also very wise and knowledgeable

Wasn't sure what to expect beforehand, but ended up loving it. Made want to be a human geography major! Her lecturing style is very captivating and easy to follow. She's very approachable and helpful, you can tell she cares about her students. Loved the assignments too! Pushes you to get out and see things. You end up learning a lot about Toronto.

Dr. Deb was a very approachable, personable, and over all great professor. I had no idea what to expect taking an urbanization course, and she made me fall in love with it. I definitely recommend taking GGR124 or any Deb Cowen course!
Great prof. Loved the lectures and the way she engaged the class. Assignments were not terribly difficult. Overall, an enjoyable class with her.

Amazing class this professor is really good. The exam was exactly like the older ones before it so study them! This class is easy and rewarding if you actually put in the effort. I enjoyed the assignments because we got to go outside and see things first hand rather than staring at books. Go to lectures and do the readings it's an easy 80%+.
Prof. Cowen is a great lecturer. The readings are interesting and the project work is sometimes geared to groups. I recommend taking any of her courses. You will not be disappointed.
as long as you put some time for work you'll be fine! I took ggr124. and she does make sure youre graded fairly, gives helpful feedback and tries hard to always improve the course
She's great compared to a lot of other profs at U of T, and the class is very interesting.

Absolutely amazing professor. Before entering the class, I had little interest in the topic but her teaching style captivates anyone and her amount of student interaction is much appreciated. I would recommend her to anyone.
The best Prof I ever had! She gave me soo much interest in geography! She made me a Urban Economic Social Geography Major. Very approachable, helpful and is really there for her students.
Lectures are interesting but the class is ridiculous. Assignments are completely unclear, TA's don't speak English, and the Professor doesn't want to answer your questions. Avoid.
